{
  "page": "Sunset Sea",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aurore_Folny_Ocean_Road.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1b/Aurore_Folny_Ocean_Road.png/300px-Aurore_Folny_Ocean_Road.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"354\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/1/1b/Aurore_Folny_Ocean_Road.png 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aurore_Folny_Ocean_Road.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Ocean_Road\" title=\"Ocean Road\">Ocean Road</a> by Aurore Folny © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Sunset Sea</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> or <b>sunset sea</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> is a sea to the west of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. It borders the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a>, and the lands <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Geography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Geography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Wildlife\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Wildlife</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Geography\">Geography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sunset_Sea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Geography\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:World_map_Westeros.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7b/World_map_Westeros.png/300px-World_map_Westeros.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"280\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7b/World_map_Westeros.png/450px-World_map_Westeros.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7b/World_map_Westeros.png/600px-World_map_Westeros.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:World_map_Westeros.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Sunset Sea is west of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> (red continent).</div></div></div>\n<p>In the south, the <a href=\"/index.php/Redwyne_Straits\" title=\"Redwyne Straits\">Redwyne Straits</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Arbor\" title=\"Arbor\">Arbor</a> divide the Sunset Sea from the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Sea\" title=\"Summer Sea\">Summer Sea</a> to the southeast. North of the Arbor is <a href=\"/index.php/Whispering_Sound\" title=\"Whispering Sound\">Whispering Sound</a> with <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Blackcrown\" title=\"Blackcrown\">Blackcrown</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Three_Towers\" title=\"Three Towers\">Three Towers</a>. Farther north in the <a href=\"/index.php/Reach\" title=\"Reach\">Reach</a> along the Sunset Sea are <a href=\"/index.php/Bandallon\" title=\"Bandallon\">Bandallon</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Shield_Islands\" title=\"Shield Islands\">Shield Islands</a>, and the mouth of the <a href=\"/index.php/Mander\" title=\"Mander\">Mander</a>. \n</p><p>The coastal <a href=\"/index.php/Ocean_Road\" title=\"Ocean Road\">Ocean Road</a> connects the Reach to the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>. Settlements of the westerlands located on the sea include <a href=\"/index.php/Crakehall\" title=\"Crakehall\">Crakehall</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisport\" title=\"Lannisport\">Lannisport</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Feastfires\" title=\"Feastfires\">Feastfires</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Kayce\" title=\"Kayce\">Kayce</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Crag\" title=\"Crag\">Crag</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Banefort\" title=\"Banefort\">Banefort</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Faircastle\" title=\"Faircastle\">Faircastle</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Fair_Isle\" title=\"Fair Isle\">Fair Isle</a>. \n</p><p>North of the westerlands in the Sunset Sea are the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Ironman%27s_Bay\" title=\"Ironman&#39;s Bay\">Ironman's Bay</a>, as well as <a href=\"/index.php/Seagard\" title=\"Seagard\">Seagard</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Cape_of_Eagles\" title=\"Cape of Eagles\">Cape of Eagles</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Priests_of_the_Drowned_God\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Priests of the Drowned God\">Priests of the Drowned God</a> consider the sea to be holy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Beyond the Iron Islands is a peninsula of the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> which includes the <a href=\"/index.php/Flint_Cliffs\" title=\"Flint Cliffs\">Flint Cliffs</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Cape_Kraken\" title=\"Cape Kraken\">Cape Kraken</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Flint%27s_Finger\" title=\"Flint&#39;s Finger\">Flint's Finger</a>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Fever_River\" title=\"Fever River\">Fever River</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Saltspear\" title=\"Saltspear\">Saltspear</a> flow into <a href=\"/index.php/Blazewater_Bay\" title=\"Blazewater Bay\">Blazewater Bay</a>. North of the peninsula are the coastlines of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rills\" title=\"Rills\">Rills</a>  and the <a href=\"/index.php/Stony_Shore\" title=\"Stony Shore\">Stony Shore</a>. Even further to the north are the <a href=\"/index.php/Bay_of_Ice\" title=\"Bay of Ice\">Bay of Ice</a> and the forests of <a href=\"/index.php/Bear_Island\" title=\"Bear Island\">Bear Island</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Sea_Dragon_Point\" title=\"Sea Dragon Point\">Sea Dragon Point</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Wolfswood\" title=\"Wolfswood\">wolfswood</a>. The Sunset Sea continues north <a href=\"/index.php/Beyond_the_Wall\" title=\"Beyond the Wall\">beyond the Wall</a> along the <a href=\"/index.php/Frozen_Shore\" title=\"Frozen Shore\">Frozen Shore</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Sunset Sea west of the <a href=\"/index.php/Lonely_Light\" title=\"Lonely Light\">Lonely Light</a> is unknown<sup id=\"cite_ref-SSM_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SSM-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> other than <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon,_Rhaenys,_and_Visenya_(islands)\" title=\"Aegon, Rhaenys, and Visenya (islands)\">Aegon, Rhaenys, and Visenya</a>, small islands two weeks southwest of Oldtown.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Wildlife\">Wildlife</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sunset_Sea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Wildlife\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Sunset Sea is roamed by swordfish, <a href=\"/index.php/Seal\" title=\"Seal\">seals</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Whale\" title=\"Whale\">whales</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Ironman%27s_Bay\" title=\"Ironman&#39;s Bay\">Ironman's Bay</a> and coastal regions are populated by various fish and shellfish.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> The north of the sea contains <a href=\"/index.php/Kraken\" title=\"Kraken\">krakens</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Leviathan\" title=\"Leviathan\">leviathans</a>, and possibly legendary <a href=\"/index.php/Sea_dragon\" title=\"Sea dragon\">sea dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Shark\" title=\"Shark\">Sharks</a> and kraken are common in the seas south of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> which include the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Sea\" title=\"Summer Sea\">Summer Sea</a> and the southern Sunset Sea.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtloiafthe_known_world.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtloiafthe_known_world.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sunset_Sea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In <i><a href=\"/index.php/Songs_the_Drowned_Men_Sing\" title=\"Songs the Drowned Men Sing\">Songs the Drowned Men Sing</a></i>, Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Kirth\" title=\"Kirth\">Kirth</a> suggested that the <a href=\"/index.php/Seastone_Chair\" title=\"Seastone Chair\">Seastone Chair</a> was created by a people from west of the Sunset Sea,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> and Archmaester <a href=\"/index.php/Haereg\" title=\"Haereg\">Haereg</a> proposed that the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> descend from these visitors.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sunset_Sea.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6a/Sunset_Sea.jpg/350px-Sunset_Sea.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"229\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/6/6a/Sunset_Sea.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sunset_Sea.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The Sunset Sea by Trevor Cook © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The ironborn of antiquity used their longships to dominate the western coast of Westeros, initially raiding the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Green_lands\" title=\"Green lands\">green lands</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> but eventually turning to conquest in the era of <a href=\"/index.php/Driftwood_king\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Driftwood king\">driftwood kings</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> During the reign of <a href=\"/index.php/Qhored_Hoare\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Qhored Hoare\">Qhored Hoare</a> the ironborn controlled the western shore of Westeros from the <a href=\"/index.php/Arbor\" title=\"Arbor\">Arbor</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Bear_Island\" title=\"Bear Island\">Bear Island</a>, but his gains were gradually lost by his descendants.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> The First Men of the continent eventually fought back with longships of their own and used stone fortifications to defend against the raiders,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_driftwood_crowns.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> and skilled <a href=\"/index.php/Andal_invasion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Andal invasion\">Andal</a> sailors accelerated the ironborn's fall.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_iron_kings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_iron_kings.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Thousands of years ago, <a href=\"/index.php/Brandon_Stark_(Shipwright)\" title=\"Brandon Stark (Shipwright)\">Brandon the Shipwright</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_in_the_North\" title=\"King in the North\">King in the North</a>, tried to sail across the Sunset Sea but was never heard from again. His son, <a href=\"/index.php/Brandon_Stark_(Burner)\" title=\"Brandon Stark (Burner)\">Brandon the Burner</a>, destroyed the northern shipyards in his grief.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Claiming the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>, King <a href=\"/index.php/Arlan_III_Durrandon\" title=\"Arlan III Durrandon\">Arlan III Durrandon</a> extended the borders of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingdom_of_the_Storm\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kingdom of the Storm\">Kingdom of the Storm</a> from the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a> in the east to the Sunset Sea in the west. However, his descendant, <a href=\"/index.php/Arrec_Durrandon\" title=\"Arrec Durrandon\">Arrec</a>, lost the riverlands to <a href=\"/index.php/Harwyn_Hoare\" title=\"Harwyn Hoare\">Harwyn Hoare</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Isles_and_the_Rivers\" title=\"King of the Isles and the Rivers\">King of the Isles and the Rivers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_stormlands:_andals_in_the_stormlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenys_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenys Targaryen\">Rhaenys Targaryen</a> once considered flying atop <a href=\"/index.php/Meraxes\" title=\"Meraxes\">Meraxes</a> to see what was beyond the Sunset Sea,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup> but she was killed during the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Dornish_War\" title=\"First Dornish War\">First Dornish War</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_dorne_against_the_dragons.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/56_AC\" title=\"56 AC\">56&#160;AC</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Elissa_Farman\" title=\"Elissa Farman\">Elissa Farman</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Hightower\" title=\"Eustace Hightower\">Eustace Hightower</a>, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Norman_Hightower\" title=\"Norman Hightower\">Norman Hightower</a> sailed west from <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a> to discover what is beyond the Sunset Sea.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <i><a href=\"/index.php/Autumn_Moon\" title=\"Autumn Moon\">Autumn Moon</a></i> sank during a storm, with some on Eustace's <i><a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Meredith\" title=\"Lady Meredith\">Lady Meredith</a></i> claiming they saw a <a href=\"/index.php/Kraken\" title=\"Kraken\">kraken</a> attack Norman's ship. Elissa's <i><a href=\"/index.php/Sun_Chaser\" title=\"Sun Chaser\">Sun Chaser</a></i> discovered the uninhabited islands Aegon, Rhaenys, and Visenya. While Eustace chose to return to Westeros, Elissa continued exploring west but was never seen again. Years later, <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> believed that he saw <i>Sun Chaser</i> in <a href=\"/index.php/Asshai\" title=\"Asshai\">Asshai</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alton_Greyjoy\" title=\"Alton Greyjoy\">Alton Greyjoy</a>, known as the Holy Fool, attempted to conquer lands beyond the <a href=\"/index.php/Lonely_Light\" title=\"Lonely Light\">Lonely Light</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_old_way_and_the_new.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_old_way_and_the_new.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Dalton_Greyjoy\" title=\"Dalton Greyjoy\">Dalton Greyjoy</a>, the Red Kraken, ruled much of the Sunset Sea during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a> until his murder at <a href=\"/index.php/Fair_Isle\" title=\"Fair Isle\">Fair Isle</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_red_kraken.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_iron_islands:_the_red_kraken.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Dagon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Dagon Greyjoy\">Dagon Greyjoy</a> also attempted to make the lands along the sea subject to the ironborn again, but was eventually defeated by <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_21-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd63.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-21\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sunset_Sea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sunset_Sea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tomasz_Jedruszek_Longship_Raider.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6b/Tomasz_Jedruszek_Longship_Raider.jpg/300px-Tomasz_Jedruszek_Longship_Raider.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"334\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6b/Tomasz_Jedruszek_Longship_Raider.jpg/450px-Tomasz_Jedruszek_Longship_Raider.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/6b/Tomasz_Jedruszek_Longship_Raider.jpg/600px-Tomasz_Jedruszek_Longship_Raider.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tomasz_Jedruszek_Longship_Raider.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Longship Raider by Tomasz Jedruszek © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Islands\" title=\"Iron Islands\">Iron Islands</a> invade the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">north</a> by attacking the <a href=\"/index.php/Harrying_of_the_Stony_Shore\" title=\"Harrying of the Stony Shore\">Stony Shore</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Fever_River\" title=\"Fever River\">Fever River</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_Deepwood_Motte\" title=\"Taking of Deepwood Motte\">Deepwood Motte</a> near the <a href=\"/index.php/Bay_of_Ice\" title=\"Bay of Ice\">Bay of Ice</a>.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sunset_Sea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsmoot\" title=\"Kingsmoot\">kingsmoot</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Gylbert_Farwynd\" title=\"Gylbert Farwynd\">Gylbert Farwynd</a>, Lord of the <a href=\"/index.php/Lonely_Light\" title=\"Lonely Light\">Lonely Light</a>, puts his name forth for <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Iron_Islands\" title=\"King of the Iron Islands\">King of the Iron Islands</a>, supported by three champions who are his sons. He promises to lead the ironborn to lands beyond the Sunset Sea where every man would be a king, but his claims are quickly dismissed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_22-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc19.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-22\">&#91;22&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The ironborn under <a href=\"/index.php/Euron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Euron Greyjoy\">Euron Greyjoy</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Isles_and_the_North\" title=\"King of the Isles and the North\">King of the Isles and the North</a>, attack the <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_the_Shields\" title=\"Taking of the Shields\">Shield Islands</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Invasion_of_the_Arbor\" title=\"Invasion of the Arbor\">Arbor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_23-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-23\">&#91;23&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sunset_Sea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>No one has ever crossed the Sunset Sea to learn what lies on the other side.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SSM_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SSM-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The sea meant freedom to the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">men of the Iron Islands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_24-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-24\">&#91;24&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>We are <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a>, the sons of the sea, chosen of the <a href=\"/index.php/Drowned_God\" title=\"Drowned God\">Drowned God</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Aeron_Greyjoy\" title=\"Aeron Greyjoy\">Aeron Greyjoy</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Gorold_Goodbrother\" title=\"Gorold Goodbrother\">Gorold Goodbrother</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Hagen</b>: If we die with dry feet, how will we find our way to the <a href=\"/index.php/Drowned_God\" title=\"Drowned God\">Drowned God</a>'s watery halls?<br />\n<b>Cromm</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Wolfswood\" title=\"Wolfswood\">These woods</a> are full of little streams. All of them lead to rivers, and all the rivers to the sea.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_25-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-25\">&#91;25&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Hagen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hagen\">Hagen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Cromm\" title=\"Cromm\">Cromm</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sunset_Sea&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot25.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_25\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 25\">Chapter 25</a>, Eddard V.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_14\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 14\">Chapter 14</a>, Catelyn II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">3.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\">3.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_1\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 1\">Chapter 1</a>, The Prophet.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtloiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtloiaf.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Lands_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"The Lands of Ice and Fire\">The Lands of Ice and Fire</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SSM-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-SSM_5-0\">5.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-SSM_5-1\">5.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/1122/\">Trade with Asshai</a>, August 26, 2000</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_